Painful experience as my 3.8 years old son (Dental square registration number 3356) had to go an emergency operation to save his life *** ** **** ****** *** ***** ******* ********* ** *** ******** ***** Please read my full honest/unbiased review before visiting the Dental Square.

I am an NRI who lives in London, recently I was in Bangalore and looking for a good dental clinic to treat the cavity for my 3.8 years old son. I enquired in my housing society (Godrej Ecity) for a good dental clinic in electronic city phase-1, some of my neighbors recommended the Dental Square Neeladari road ecity branch. So I visited the clinic on Dec 7th 2019 and met Dr Sneha and Dr Jayanthi. Dr Sneha started the RCT/Pulpectomy treatment for son first on right lower tooth on 12th Dec and after 3 days on left side lower tooth. My son started having the swelling on right side from 19th Dec 2019 onwards, this started increasing day by day, ***** ******* **** *** **** ** **** ** *** ******** ** **** ******** ******* ***** * ***** I lost the trust on the experience of these doctors and started consulting my relative who works as a pediatrician ** ***** *** ****** ** ******* ** ** *** ********** *** ** *** ***** **** ** *** ********** *** ********** ****** *** ******** ** *** ***** *** *** ** *** ******* ** *** **** ****** ************* ****** ***** *** ******* ********** ******** *** my son had 102 fever on/off in few hours, the situation deteriorated further as these doctors stopped answering the emails or phone calls *** ***** ** *** ****** **** ** ***** ******** I had to admit my son ** ******* ******** *********** on 24th Dec 2019 for an emergency operation to remove the pus as infection started in his whole body which was a life threatening situation. ** ******* ********* ********** ******** ** ******* ********** ****** ******** operated my son on 25th Dec 2019 and now my son is recovering from this surgery. This costed my 40,000 INR for the operation, so much pain to my son as this was done in General anesthesia, you can only imagine what kid of pain we have experienced.whole incid. ** *** ********* ****** **** ** *** ***** ***** ******* doctors are not sharing the x-ray report soft copy with me ** **** **** **** **** ***** *** ******* *** ****** Now I don’t know what to do next as my son’s both side tooth conditions are in very bad shape and we can not afford another root canal ** **** *** ******* *** ***** ********** *** ****** ***** ** **** ******* this has made my son’s life completely difficult and now we are in painful situation.*************** ****** ****** *********** **** *** ******** ********** **** ** ***** *** ** **** ** * ****** ** **** ****** ******* **** ****** *** ***** ******* ****** ******* **** *** ******* *** *** *** ********* **** ********** ** **** ******** ***** **** ******** ** ** **** * ***** **** *** **** ******* ***** ******* *** ******** ****** *********** ** ****** *** ************ ** **** ****** *** ******** ******* ** ***** ********
